u. You're coming with me.' To me he said, 'Put some pant\n\n- David Wong, This Book Is Full of Spiders: Seriously, Dude, Don't Touch It\n|\nAsk questions. The secrets of life are hidden in questions, so ask wisely.\n\n- Mensah\n|\nHappiness is something you lay siege to, it is a battle like a game of go. I will take hold of all the pain and snuff it out.\n\n- Shan Sa, The Girl Who Played Go\n|\nEthan Wyeth: I hope you're thirsty.'Gideon Wyeth:'Why?'Ethan: 'Cause your dumb and ugly, but I can do something about thirsty.\n\n- Orson\n|\nYou must ask and meditate, after which the Holy Spirit will awaken your spirit to be joined with Him\n\n- Sunday\n|\nThe greater part of our happiness or misery depends upon our dispositions, and not upon our circumstances.\n\n- Martha"